<br>
Rules are as follows (keep in mind this is just a suggestion being thrown to the critics)<br>
<br>
LOOT: A: As leader I/he/she gets 2 rolls on what ever items I CAN USE! If i win an item on my first roll i am done.<br>
B: Melee (ranger, beast lord, shadow knight, paladin, warrior, and monk) will be able to roll on CoF. If more than one drops everyone who didn't win ( out of melee classes ) gets to roll again.<br>
C: Paly epic peice, all paladins get a roll BUT this is theyre only roll ( if they choose to roll ) for all loot. If more than one drops then all that didnt win ( out of paladins ) get another roll.<br>
D: Red dragon scale, all warriors and bards ( that choose to roll ) are in on this if more than one drops then all that didnt win ( out of warrior and bards ) get another roll.<br>
E: Bag drops, ONLY monks and casters will get to roll on the bags if more than one drops then ONLY casters will get to roll on second, third, etc. <br>
<br>
ALL other drops will only be rolled on by the indicated casters.<br>
<br>
To summarize one small thing. YOU will only be able to roll on one item BUT if more than one drops you will have another chance unless you are a monk and a bag drops.<br>
<br>
Classes that will roll on other loots are as follows:<br>
Clerics, Druids, Enchanters, Shaman, and Wizards<br>
<br>
Now for a tiny bit of extra incentive for casters most needed but hardly ever want to go. Those classes are : Clerics, Druids, Enchanters, Shaman, and Wizards<br>
<br>
All items that are used in casting such as jewels for symbols, coffins for corpse summoning, and any others that i am missing, Will be reimbursed or handed out at the beggining of the raid. ALSO if voted for by all raiders a cash charge will occur for raffel to be rolled on by only casters! A donation fee will be asked of all raiders, except casters, of the minimum 25p per raider or i/he/she( leader ) will have a item of somewhat high value to be rolled on by casters only.<br>
<br>
Now for grouping and classes needed<br>
Total number of groups: 6-7<br>
Total number of people: 35-45<br>
Casters needed.<br>
2 enchanters ( at least )<br>
2 Shaman ( at least )<br>
2 Wizards ( at least )<br>
2 Clerics ( at least )<br>
2 Druids ( at least )<br>
1 magician <br>
1 Necromancer ( at least )<br>
Total: 12<br>
<br>
Melee<br>
8 Warriors includes MA and SA<br>
8 Monks includes 2 Pullers and 2 taggers<br>
The rest can be made up of hybrid melees<br>
Total: 16+<br>
<br>
This leaves alot of slots still open for any others that want to join in.<br>
<br>
